  "description": "The bird was about the same size as all the Black-crowned Night-Herons around it.It had a gray bill. It was black on its throat. From its head all the way to its feet was a gray color. I did not see its feet because it was standing and then sitting in the nest.The very top of its head was a cream yellow color (Bavarian cream). It had a red eye and its lores and eye stripe were black. It also had a white cheek stripe.Behaviors: When we first saw the bird it happened to be standing. After a little while it sat down and never stood the rest of the time we were there. Overall it was not very active.Call: I did not hear a song.Plumage: Adult",
